# ============================================================================
# tqc-client — minimal track-set for rollback of OUR code changes only.
# Push: C# scripts, tolua framework patches, Editor diagnostic scripts,
#       Plugins (patched tolua.bundle), ProjectSettings, Packages.
# Skip: Library/Temp cache, game IP assets (Texture2D/Mesh/Material/scenes),
#       extracted Lua source (_Assets/), bundle staging data.
# ============================================================================

# === Unity standard ignores ===
[Ll]ibrary/
[Tt]emp/
[Oo]bj/
[Bb]uild/
[Bb]uilds/
[Ll]ogs/
[Uu]ser[Ss]ettings/
[Mm]emoryCaptures/
[Rr]ecordings/

# Burst compiler
*.pidb.meta
*.pdb.meta
*.mdb.meta
sysinfo.txt
*.apk
*.aab
*.unitypackage
*.app

# Crash reports
*.stackdump
*.blob
mono_crash.*
crashlytics-build.properties

# Visual Studio / Rider IDE / VS Code
.vs/
.idea/
.vscode/
*.csproj
*.sln
*.unityproj
*.user
*.userosscache
*.suo
*.tmp
*.pidb
*.booproj
*.svd
*.pdb
*.mdb
*.opendb
*.VC.db

# OS
.DS_Store
._*
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
ehthumbs_vista.db

# === Project-specific ===
# CDN bundle download cache (downloaded at runtime, not source)
CdnCache/

# Loose dev artifacts at project root
_first_open.log
game_view.png
*.log

# AssetRipper artifacts — Premium (licensed) generates timestamped log files
# (Leftover "AssetRipper.GUI.Free.log" pattern was from earlier Free trial; we use Premium now.)
AssetRipper.GUI.Free.log
AssetRipper.GUI.Premium.log
AssetRipper_*.log

# ============================================================================
# Assets/ selective tracking — exclude game IP, keep our code + patches.
# Pattern: ignore everything under Assets/, then UN-ignore specific subdirs.
# Keep both the directory and its sibling .meta file (Unity GUID link).
# ============================================================================
/Assets/*
!/Assets/.gitignore
!/Assets/.gitkeep

# OUR work — code, patches, editor tooling
!/Assets/Scripts/
!/Assets/Scripts.meta
!/Assets/Source/
!/Assets/Source.meta
!/Assets/ToLua/
!/Assets/ToLua.meta
!/Assets/Editor/
!/Assets/Editor.meta
!/Assets/Plugins/
!/Assets/Plugins.meta

# Unity-internal small dirs that hold project-level settings (not game IP)
!/Assets/Scenes/
!/Assets/Scenes.meta

# Shaders: 1-1 reverse-engineered from APK GLSL bytecode (our code, not raw
# IP assets). 3500+ Role ETC1 variants are byte-identical → git delta-compresses
# to ~270KB. Worth versioning as rollback/backup of the shader port pipeline.
!/Assets/Shader/
!/Assets/Shader.meta
# Resources/ stays ignored (game-IP prefabs) EXCEPT our ported shaders subtree.
!/Assets/Resources/
/Assets/Resources/*
!/Assets/Resources/shaders/
!/Assets/Resources.meta

# (Explicitly skipped — game IP / large / not edited by us)
# /Assets/AnimationClip/    /Assets/AnimatorController/   /Assets/Avatar/
# /Assets/Cubemap/          /Assets/Font/                 /Assets/GameObject/
# /Assets/GooglePlayPlugins/ /Assets/Material/            /Assets/Mesh/
# /Assets/MonoBehaviour/    /Assets/RenderTexture/        /Assets/Resources/
# /Assets/Shader/           /Assets/Sprite/               /Assets/StreamingAssets/
# /Assets/TextAsset/        /Assets/Texture2D/            /Assets/_Assets/
# /Assets/_artist/          /Assets/resources_bundle/     /Assets/textmesh/
# /Assets/textmesh pro/
